Hi Guys, I am also facing the same issue in this weeks. After quite debugging we found that the formulae format which we are creating is like:
worksheet.getCell('A1').dataValidation = {
    type: 'list',
    allowBlank: true,
    formulae: ["One,Two,Three,Four"]
};

but the expected format is:
worksheet.getCell('A1').dataValidation = {
    type: 'list',
    allowBlank: true,
    formulae: ['"One,Two,Three,Four"']
};
means with a single quote and double quote. So this solves our issue.

After a few days again we faced the same issue, this time we found that the string length which we are passing is quite large 400+ characters, in such case also this error is found. Then we overcome this issue by using another way data validation creation i.e using the dedicated column for data validation values.
In this solution we first add all values in the last column i.e Z then hide this column using the hidden property and then add the data validation as:
worksheet.getCell('A1').dataValidation = {
    type: 'list',
    allowBlank: true,
    formulae: ["$Z$1-$Z$10"]
};
I hope either of these cases causing issues in your application and the solution works well, Thanks!
